(1154, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1139, 'Ticket', NULL, '<p>Based only upon the photographs, the damage to the Ford left front is relatively consistent with the damage to the VW right front.The damage on the Ford left front is in an area that could have come in contact with the Volkswagen while the vehicles were in a specific orientation at impact.</p><p></p><p>1. Is either vehicle available for inspection?</p><p>2. Are there any detailed statements from the drivers that identify the paths of travel of both vehicles just before impact or the positions of the vehicles at impact?</p><p>3. Was the Ford driver attempting a left turn, going straight, or making a right turn at the intersection?</p><p></p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-03 22:16:07', 107, 'Chris Borelli', 'cborelli@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1155, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1139, 'Ticket', NULL, '<p>Vehicles are no longer available and the claimant is not being cooperative.  \r\n\r\nThe insured/Taurus claims he was going straight, but I''m not sure I believe him. He has changed his story several times.</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-03 23:11:00', 100, 'Bali Lyons', 'lyonscars@mac.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1156, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1139, 'Ticket', NULL, '<p>Without an inspection of either vehicle I cannot rule out the possibility of contact between the vehicles if the Ford was angled to the left, as if the driver was attempting a left turn.</p><p></p><p>Paul,</p><p>I would like to see the individual photos and attachments grouped together under &quot;Ford&quot; or &quot;insured vehicle&quot; or &quot;insured''s Ford&quot; heading. It will not always be obvious which vehicle the photo goes with. The enlarged photo when hovering over the thumbnail is excellent.</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-04 13:13:39', 107, 'Chris Borelli', 'cborelli@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1157, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1139, 'Ticket', NULL, '<p>Ok I see what you mean. Did you have any trouble navigating the portal? I think it could use some improvement. Anything else you can think of let me know!</p><p></p><p>My dad was coaching me on the answers. He was trying to be difficult.</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-04 17:23:22', 80, 'Paul Lyons', 'paul@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1158, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1139, 'Ticket', NULL, '<p>Also should we come up with a template you guys could fill out and submit for the final review? Something the insurance user could download and print.</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-04 17:25:57', 80, 'Paul Lyons', 'paul@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1159, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1139, 'Ticket', NULL, '<p>There is a little icon for keeping track of time right below your name at the top of the assignment. Its probably not the best location. Could you go back and mark off the amount of time you spent answering the question? We will keep this information private.</p><p></p><p></p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-04 17:30:44', 80, 'Paul Lyons', 'paul@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1160, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1140, 'Discussion', NULL, '<p>I just realized that this is where we are suppose to communicate about the assignments. There is an option for &quot;discuss this job&quot; in the menu to the right of the job details.</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-04 17:32:30', 80, 'Paul Lyons', 'paul@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1161, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1124, 'Ticket', NULL, '<p>No files with assignment</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-06 20:12:08', 107, 'Chris Borelli', 'cborelli@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1162, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1140, 'Discussion', NULL, '<p>Paul, Is there a screen that shown only the jobs assigned to me? I think as each technician logs on, the screen should be &quot;our&quot; screen. Although we should be able to access all the jobs and assign ourselves and others work, the default screen should list the jobs already assigned to us (by company, date, or other variables)</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-06 20:19:26', 107, 'Chris Borelli', 'cborelli@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1163, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1140, 'Discussion', NULL, '<p>I dont think there is a screen to view jobs that are only assigned to you, but there is a way to create custom themes for each user so this could be accomplished later on.  There is a lot of room for improvement to our backend. </p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-07 14:48:10', 80, 'Paul Lyons', 'paul@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1164, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1140, 'Discussion', NULL, '<p>Paul - relative to what Chris said, maybe the default page could open with all the jobs, but then you could just have a filter system where you click on any of our names, and it would filter out and display only jobs assigned to that name.</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-08 17:02:05', 110, 'jsiegfried@accidentreview.com', 'jsiegfried@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1165, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1140, 'Discussion', NULL, '<p>Jim- you can view jobs that are only assigned to you by clicking on &quot;assignments&quot; in the top menu after signing in. I didnt realize this earlier because the guys who set this up use the term assignment and job interchangeably. We should decide which term we want to use then update the site so only one term is used.</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-08 17:19:37', 80, 'Paul Lyons', 'paul@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(1166, NULL, 'Comment', 'resources', 30, NULL, 1140, 'Discussion', NULL, '<p>Jim - When we do get to the point where we are creating custom themes for each user it might be possible to set the default page to display all assignments.</p>', NULL, 3, 1, NULL, '2013-01-08 17:28:32', 80, 'Paul Lyons', 'paul@accidentreview.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
