(545, 1, '2012-02-29 20:38:42', '2012-02-29 20:38:42', '<p><strong><a class="contentlink" href="mailto:jsiegfried@sdlyons.com" id="JamesSiegfried" name="JamesSiegfried">James Siegfried</a></strong> is a Mechanical Engineer (B.M.S.E.), receiving his primary education from the University of Rhode Island in Kingston, Rhode Island. He specializes in vehicle fire origin and cause and is a Certified Fire and Explosion Investigator (CFEI) and a Certified Vehicle Fire Investigator (CVFI), as certified through the National Association of Fire Investigators (NAFI). Mr. Siegfried has over 10 years experience examining, reviewing, and analyzing vehicular fires. In addition, he has extensive training and experience in analysis of vehicle mechanical failures, thefts, and anti-theft security devices. He receives continuing education and performs continuous research in the fields of fire origin and cause and mechanical and electronic vehicle security systems.</p>', 'James Siegfried', 'Certified Vehicle Fire Investigator', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'james-siegfried', '', '', '2012-03-01 18:47:43', '2012-03-01 18:47:43', '', 0, '/?post_type=technician-bio&#038;p=545', 0, 'technician-bio', '', 0),
