(547, 1, '2012-02-29 20:39:27', '2012-02-29 20:39:27', '<p><strong><a class="contentlink" href="mailto:lpeck@sdlyons.com" id="LouisPeck" name="LouisPeck">Louis R. Peck</a></strong> is a Mechanical Engineer (M.S.M.E.) and an Accident Reconstructionist. He received his Master of Science from the Worcester Polytechnic Institute in Worcester, Massachusetts, where his studies focused on impact mechanics, roadside safety, and predicting human injury in automotive collisions. Mr. Peck received his primary education in accident reconstruction from the Northwestern University in Chicago, Illinois, and receives continuing education at various universities and related associations around the country. He has also developed a nationally distributed software package for analyzing low-speed vehicular impacts, and has recently released a program to predict vehicle behavior during a utility pole impact. Mr. Peck is also trained in the latest Nikon Total Station mapping equipment and Vista FX accident reconstruction software.</p>', 'Louis R. Peck', 'Accident Reconstructionist', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'louis-r-peck', '', '', '2012-03-01 18:47:22', '2012-03-01 18:47:22', '', 0, '/?post_type=technician-bio&#038;p=547', 0, 'technician-bio', '', 0),
